Author: cevr <seeve.c@gmail.com>
Date:   Wed Jun 17 15:35:52 2026 -0400

    feat(forms)(form-engine): generic decoder + renderer + action skeleton + tests

    Branch 6.2 (ADR 0007). Lands the form engine the contact/volunteer/
    registration routes migrate onto in 6.3-6.5, all driven by the closed
    FormDefinition (6.1) read through Content.getForm (Branch 5):

    - decode.ts: definitionToSchema compiles a FormDefinition into the
      Effect Schema codec that validates its submissions, reproducing the
      hand-tuned annotation idiom (empty/absent/invalid-type each emit a real
      MessageKey, the true/false/on checkbox-boolean codec, discriminated-
      variant presence as a struct-level filter, requiredWhenEquals cross-
      field rules). decodeForm reuses parseSchema/formatSchemaResult so the
      generated Issue tree buckets through one shared boundary.
    - render.tsx: <FormFields> renders the closed FieldKind set, projecting
      bilingual Text to the active locale, nested groups under dotted
      group.field names, and the variant discriminator with client-driven
      conditional branch fields.
    - action.ts: formAction({ form, notify, success }) wraps routeFormAction
      with getForm -> decodeForm -> notify -> toast.redirect. notify stays a
      separable callback so Branch 7's persist step lands in front of it.
    - tests: decode (each kind + cross-field + variant + error-path keys),
      render (each kind + locale + variant branch switching), action
      (notify+redirect wiring, notify-failure, honeypot short-circuit).

